description:
Abraham left his shameful past in Egypt to a new beginning in the promised land. He was rich and blessed by God, loaded with gifts from the king of Egypt. Wherever he pitched his tent, Abraham, the friend of God, also built an altar, calling all within his camp to morning and evening sacrifice. Despite his riches, Abraham chose the path of peace and unselfishness in his conflict with Lot. Watch Francois DuPlessis present on Abraham's life and character as he enters and settles in the promised land.
